cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scheduling tasks on multiple servers in a distributed computing framework.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for optimizing task scheduling.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper deals with optimizing the completion time of a job, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possibility as the paper aims to improve the performance of MapReduce jobs.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the approximation ratio of the proposed algorithm.
